properties.headline: SPECIAL EVENT CLEARWAYS - The Rocks Markets - THE ROCKS George St between Hickson Rd AND Lower Fort St
properties.otherAdvice:
Long term special event clearway parking restrictions will be in effect on George St in The Rocks to accommodate the weekly Rocks Markets.

Clearways will be in effect every weekend from 10pm Friday until 10pm Sunday on the eastern side of George St between Hickson Rd and Lower Fort St.

Clearways are strict no-parking zones and apply even to local residents or Mobility Scheme Permit holders. Check signs before parking as vehicles left in clearways will be towed and a fee applies.

Road closures will also be in place on weekends for the markets from 4am Saturday until 10pm Sunday on sections on Argyle St, Artherden St, George St, Kendall Lane, Mill Lane and Playfair St.
properties.displayName: SPECIAL EVENT CLEARWAYS - The Rocks Markets

properties.headline: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS - Easter school holiday period - SHOALHAVEN Booderee Ave, Illowra Lane at Hyams Beach
properties.otherAdvice:
Changed traffic conditions including a new roundabout under traffic control at the intersection of Booderee Avenue and Illowra Lane, speed reductions will be in place to manage the heavy traffic over the Easter school holiday period. 

A speed reduction from 80km/h to 40km/h will be in effect along Booderee Ave in both directions.

If Hyams Beach reaches capacity, or in the event of a catastrophic fire danger rating, temporary closures at Booderee Ave may be implemented. 

Motorists should arrive early or expect significant delays on roads approaching the township and beach during this period.  

Alternative white sand beaches can be found at Shoalhaven – South Coast NSW.
properties.displayName: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS - Easter school holiday period

arrangementAttachments.linkName: Anzac Day 2021 road closure and transport map

properties.otherAdvice:
Special event clearways will be in effect on both sides of Abercrombie St between O'Connor St and Broadway on Sunday 25 April from 5:30am until 9am to accommodate Anzac Day transport operations. 

Major roads will be closed and clearways will also be in effect throughout the city - details here. 

Clearways are strict no-parking zones and apply even to local residents, businesses or RMS Mobility Scheme Permit holders. Vehicles left in clearways will be towed and a fee applies so check signs carefully on the day and the night before as clearways come into effect in the early morning.
